The paper focuses on personalized attention prediction using a convolutional network for saliency detection in images. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques and human-computer interaction (HCI) aspects, which are covered by the cs.CV and cs.HC sub-categories, respectively. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning (ML) techniques for training the model, which falls under the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with multimedia (MM) data in the form of images, which is covered by the cs.MM sub-category.
